            "id": 6388,
            "user": {
                "id": 256,
                "name": "keMoN"
            },
            "notes": "Is it really necessary to permanently display the XP count and level? \r\nIt's not really providing you any information, at least the levels aren't. All of that can be checked in the limbo menu.\r\n\r\nIf the XP gain feedback is necessary, we could also simply display the amount that is gained. \r\nFor example on a kill you display \"+3\" somewhere.\r\n\r\n",
            "created_on": "2017-02-11T20:55:51Z",
            "details": []
        },
        {
            "id": 6389,
            "user": {
                "id": 140,
                "name": "Spyhawk"
            },
            "notes": "keMoN wrote:\r\n> If the XP gain feedback is necessary, we could also simply display the amount that is gained. \r\n> For example on a kill you display \"+3\" somewhere.\r\n\r\nThis is a great suggestion. A simpler way to handle the issue is to only display the XPs earn in current map (or XP earn in campaign if using campaign mode) as it is already done with the end of game stats / awards.\r\nLet's kill XP save slowly but surely. :P",
            "created_on": "2017-02-11T21:20:06Z",
            "details": []
        },
        {
            "id": 6390,
            "user": {
                "id": 256,
                "name": "keMoN"
            },
            "notes": "Seems good to me. However, what to do with the scoreboard? Also only display the gained XP or the total accumulated XP of the profile? Showing only the gained XP allows for proper comparison and the rank icon still gives rough insight on the total accumulated XP of a player.\r\n\r\nSo the players don't freak out, the total accumulated XP are still in the limbo menu, along with the levels.",
            "created_on": "2017-02-11T21:35:45Z",
            "details": []
        },
        {
            "id": 6391,
            "user": {
                "id": 256,
                "name": "keMoN"
            },
            "notes": "",
