        {
            "id": 6393,
            "user": {
                "id": 140,
                "name": "Spyhawk"
            },
            "notes": "I think we can safely replace the total XPs on limbo menu too. People want to be able to compare XPs, so let's keep the total on scoreboard for now... once the Rating system is fully implemented/tested and the ranks system adjusted, we can kill it for good. Hopefully before the next release :P\r\n\r\nRelevant commits:\r\n* https://dev.etlegacy.com/projects/etlegacy/repository/revisions/2d569c8065e169b9f87e248767ea0a252c3f8a12/diff/\r\n* https://dev.etlegacy.com/projects/etlegacy/repository/revisions/179e058b12898c82010967fda6a2a394b02d742f/diff/src/game/g_stats.c\r\n\r\n{TODO}\r\n* -Show current map/campaign XPs on HUD, limbo, scoreboard, end game stats-\r\n* -Fix scoreboard rank algorithm-\r\n* -Use 4 XP digits (limbo, scoreboard, HUD adjustment) - we don't need more and we gain extra space on scoreboard!-",
            "created_on": "2017-02-11T22:05:20Z",
            "details": []
        },
        {
            "id": 6394,
            "user": {
                "id": 256,
                "name": "keMoN"
            },
            "notes": "I still think that in the scoreboard, it is better to have only the XP earned in this map/campaign, as it gives you complete comparison over the actual ranking of player scores and not just time played. The ranks are still indicators for time played, so you wouldn't lose that information entirely. The limbo menu in my eyes acts like the player profile Atleast until I can find the time and motivation to burry myself in the menu UI code, to create a proper player menu with stats and shit. So the limbo menu should give you the absolute XP count along with your levels, in my eyes.\r\n\r\nHowever, if your rank system really gets ready for the next release, this doesn't matter anyway. Bye, bye XP  :P",
            "created_on": "2017-02-12T11:15:09Z",
            "details": []
        },
